Methods in prolog that return Term
static Term Init.askProlog(Term Goal)
          Asks Prolog a query Goal and returns the first solution of the form "the(Answer)" , where Answer is an instance of Goal or the constant "no" if no solution exists
static Term Init.askProlog(Term Answer, Term Body)
          Asks Prolog a query Answer, Goal and returns the first solution of the form "the(Answer)" or the constant "no" if no solution exists
